Publicly-held entities are required to report certain information about their business segments. In the <em>Segment Reporting Essentials</em> course, we cover the tests used to determine reportable segments and cover all of the associated disclosures, including entity-wide disclosures and those targeted at specific segments. The discussion is accompanied by a number of examples, including an extract from an actual public company filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission.

